g.text: Under- and Over-sampling techniques are often mentioned in presence of
unbalanced datasets. Many Machine Learning algorithms suffer from data
imbalance, therefore they comes into help in such a cases.
Over-sampling allows to upsample the minority class, duplicating
or generating new data samples, decreasing the gap with the
Under-sampling allows to downsample the majority class, removing
random or redundant instances. This approach may be suitable
only in presence of large datasets and without a very big gap
Hybrid techniques employs both upsampling and downsampling,
taking advantages of the pros of both techniques
